Package StratmasClient.substrate

Class Summary
CircleMaker This class implements methods used to construct and modify circles
ColorChooser This class is used to select a color from the color map and fill arbitrary shapes.
ColorMap This is the color map used in the substrate editor.
ColorMapDialog ColorMapDialog is used to set color map options for a process variable in SubstrateEditor.
ColorMapLabel This class is used to paint the color map.
ColorMapValuesLabel This class is used to draw the color map values.
CreateFactionDialog This dialog is used to create factions.
DisplayControl This class is used to create GUI components used in StratmasEditor.
PointedValueLabel Displays the value on the color map pointed by the mouse cursor.
PolygonMaker This class implements methods used to construct, change and move polygonials.
SelectShapeDialog The dialog used to select input shape file for SubstrateEditor.
ShapeMaker This class implements methods used to construct, change and move shapes.
ShapeValuePair This class is used to represent shapes with their values.
SubstrateEditor This class implements the substrate editor.
SubstrateMapDrawer This class is used to display shapes for regions and population centers as well as to create new shapes.
SubstrateXMLReader This class is used to read XML files needed for SubstrateEditor.
SubstrateXMLWriter This class is used to write XML files needed for SubstrateEditor.
TickLabel This class is used to paint ticks on the color map.
